param.dialogReference: Output point feature class containing the highest points returned by the tool.

tool.summary: Finds the highest point (or points if several have the same elevation) of the input surface within a defined area.
tool.usage:
• This tool requires Spatial Analyst.

  • The output may contain more than one highest point.

  • The output contains a field named elevation with the elevation value of the highest point.

  • The units of the highest elevation point match the z (elevation) units of the Input Surface. Check the Input Surface's metadata for this unit.

  • Multiple input areas return one elevation value.
